title: Medical Colleagues of Texas Road Race
Sun & Ski Pure Austin Crit Series
2006 Yeti Cycle / Mad Duck Bar-H Bash
directions:
The Breaks is located 80 miles north of the Dallas/Ft. Worth Metroplex, five miles northeast of the small town of St. Jo, Texas on FM 2382.

From the Dallas/Ft. Worth area drive north on I-35 to Gainesville. Drive west on Hwy 82 to St. Jo (23 miles). Turn right at the Dairy Queen onto FM 2382 and drive north for 4.5 miles. Look for the bikes on the fence and go left on County Road 433 (gravel). Go down the hill one mile and look for the old 1942 fat tire bicycle on the left. The camping area, restroom facilities and self-pay station are just inside the entrance.

description: SFA is hosting a dual event collegiate mountain bike race. Contact Adam Allen 936-371-9818 (Cheifallen97@msn.com)
course: Short track XC Course is held at local city park. .5 mile course with many short climbs and one long climb per lap. XC course held next to campus, 4 mile loop with lots of up and down action. Some very tricky up and downhill sections.
registration: 2 hours before the race starts each day with pre registration the night before on the SFA campus. Registration closes 15 mins prior to each event starting.
notes: Saturday XC... 5 laps for Men\\\'s A, 4 laps for Men\\\'s B, 3 laps for Men\\\'s C...
directions: (College Station) Hwy 21 to Nacogdoches, Turn left on University dr and head north to SFA Campus, park in parking lot by William R Johnson Arena. (Waco) East on hwy 84 to Mt Enterprise, south on Hwy 259 to Nacogdoches. Once in city, turn left on east College st til you see William R Johnson Arena. (Houston) Hwy 59 north to Nacogdoches, Bus 59 into Nac, right on east College to Johnson Arena.

Sun and Ski Presents the Rocky Hill Roundup
description:
Sun and Ski Presents The Rocky Hill Roundup
Part of the TMBRA Fall Cup Series
September 24, 2006
Rocky Hill Ranch, Smithville, Texas
course: Multiple laps of 7-10 mile mostly singletrack course. Shorter course for 12 and unders.
registration:
Online available at Bikereg.com, or
mail in form for Fall Cup available at TMBRA.org
Pre-reg entry fees are $30 for adults, $15 for Juniors 13-18, $10 for 12 and under...$5 more day of race for adults only. There will be a price entry fee difference of $5 for Non-NORBA members.
notes:
Sport classes at 0900
Expert classes at 1100
Beginner classes at 1:30
directions: Rocky Hill Ranch is on FM 153, 2 miles north of Hwy 71.

title: Copperas Cove Skill Based Road Race Championship
Fall High School Cycling Benefit Race
description: Fall USCF race to benefit North Texas High School club cycling.
course: The Reasource Connection (Fort Worth Wednesday Night Crit) perimeter road.  1.6 mile loop - no corners and wide, sweeping turns.
registration: $15 at Bike Reg and $25 on-site for Senior Riders / $10 pre-reg and $15 on-site for Junior events.  Second event is $10.
notes:
The race will benefit the North Texas High School Cycling League and is promoted by The Racing Post and hosted by The Resource Connection of Tarrant County

High School events are scored by the top three riders from each school and awards are given to top three schools
directions: I20 and Campus drive - north to The Reasource Connect.
